  "prompt": "Does Reliance JIO 4G require internet to make voice calls?",
  "response": "Yes, Reliance Jio 4G uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology for voice calls, which means that it requires an internet connection to make voice calls. When you make a call on a Jio network, your voice is transmitted as data over the LTE network rather than through traditional circuit-switched methods used in older networks. This allows for better call quality and the ability to use data services simultaneously while on a call. However, it's worth noting that the voice calls themselves do not incur additional charges, as they are included in the data packages offered by Jio.",
